oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Likens family children
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Siblings Tommy Likens, age 8 or 9 (1899-1975), Dona B. Likens (1906-1907) and Nora Mae Likens Smith, age 5 (1902-1975). Baby Dona is deceased and dressed for burial. Adults are holding umbrellas over the children to keep the sun off of them.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Families; Funeral rites & ceremonies
